<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Minister-Counselor of Embassy in China (
                        Clark
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1949v08</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d948</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">948</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1949-07-22T08:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1949-07-22T08:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-07-22T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-07-22T08:00:00-05:00" n="948" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d948">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Stuart, J. Leighton: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister-Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clark</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-07-22T21:00:00+08:00">July 22, 1949—9 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 10:30 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Cantel 801. Urge desirability advance information Canton for release here at
                    proper time by Connors<note n="27" xml:id="d948fn27">W. Bradley Connors, Attaché
                        in China.</note> of publicity contemplated Deptel 825, July 20 to Nanking,
                    repeated Canton telCan 470. Advance knowledge details Department’s plans and <hi rend="italic">en clair</hi> message re release would be most valuable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clark</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
